th_favorite</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/TCfCqln</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[jcmoney1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Good parents should always support their children</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/esq2kgK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UWchdex.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thanks, Bill! #imgur13</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/esq2kgK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[drestinblack]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My 13th Favourite Post, Shamelessly Reposted</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/pgvvU9o</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/b26fSvD.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Bruce Wayne
4.5 oz. black iced coffee 
2 oz bourbon 
0.25–0.5 oz. maple syrup (depending how sweet you like it) 
Brew a pot of coffee and let chill until cold, or dilute cold-brew coffee concentrate with an equal amount of cold water. Measure all ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice and shake thoroughly, until chilled and foamy. Strain into glass over ice. Serves 1</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/V2MmTJH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Boy Wonder
3 oz. orange juice 
2 oz. sparkling wine 
1 oz. silver tequila 
Splash grenadine or maraschino cherry juice 
Pour tequila, juice, and sparkling wine into a champagne flute and stir. Tilt glass slightly and slowly pour grenadine down the side so that it settles at the bottom. Garnish with a lime slice. Serves 1</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/smgONQU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Joker
3 oz. grape Jolly Rancher-infused vodka (see below) 
0.25 oz. lime juice 
Seltzer 
To make the infused vodka: Unwrap 10–12 purple Jolly Ranchers and put them in a sealable jar or bottle. Add 1½ cups of vodka, seal, shake, and let sit overnight or until candy fully dissolves when you shake the bottle. Chill until ready to use. 
Add 3 oz. infused vodka and lime juice to a Collins glass with ice, stir, and fill with seltzer. Garnish with lime slice. Serves 1

Edit: Alternative to the jolly rancher infused vodka is to just make a regular Gin and Tonic with the Empress 1908 Gin (https://www.empressgin.com/). It gets the same shade of wicked cool purple.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3y50B4F.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Poison Ivy
2 oz. gin 
1 oz. St. Germain 
0.75 oz. fresh-squeezed lime juice 
3 sprigs fresh basil 
2 sprigs fresh mint 
Muddle all ingredients well in a cocktail shaker. Fill with ice, shake vigorously for at least 20 seconds (this will help break up the herbs and give the drink its color and flavor), and strain into a coupe glass. Serves 1</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/avz0T2L.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Mr. Freeze
6 oz. pineapple juice 
1.5 oz. white rum 
1.5 oz. blue Curaçao 
3–4 blue raspberry Jolly Rancher candies (optional) 
The night before making: Divide pineapple juice between sections of an ice cube tray and freeze until solid. Crush Jolly Rancher candies with a mortar and pestle, or seal in a plastic bag and crush with a rolling pin or another heavy kitchen tool. Empty “crystals” onto a small plate. Rub the rim of a margarita or hurricane glass with a lime slice and roll it in the candy crystals to coat, then chill glass in fridge or freezer while you blend the cocktail. Combine frozen pineapple juice cubes, rum, and blue Curaçao in a blender, pulse to break up the frozen juice, and blend until smooth. Pour into glass. Serve with a straw (and maybe a spoon). Serves 1

EDIT: Alternative to the blue raspberry Jolly Rancher is to just make your own blue crystal methamphetamine a la Breaking Bad. If you don't have home made meth, getting it from your local fried chicken restaurant is fine too. Remember to support your local meth heads!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZzGJtil.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Catwoman
2 oz. bourbon whiskey 
1 oz. sweet vermouth 
0.5 oz. creme de cassis 
0.5 oz. fresh-squeezed lemon juice 
Dash bitters Shake all ingredients vigorously with ice and strain into a martini glass (or serve on the rocks, if your prefer). Serves 1</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xZOYO39.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Alfred
2 cups Pimm’s No. 1 
3 cups brewed black tea, chilled 
2 12-oz. bottles ginger beer, like Reed’s or Gosling’s 
1 lemon 
1 orange 
6 sprigs fresh mint, plus more for glass garnishes 
Wash lemon and orange and slice them into thin rounds. Add citrus, Pimm’s and tea to a large pitcher, stir, and keep in the fridge at least one hour or until chilled. To serve, stir in ginger beer, pour into glasses filled with ice, and garnish with mint and a lemon slice. Optional: If you’d like a boozier drink, add 1 oz. of gin to your glass before serving, and then stir in the Pimm’s mixture. Serves 8

EDIT: If you can't find ginger beer, you can always substitute ginger ale or root beer.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/uSTJmyh.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sauce: http://www.buzzfeed.com/rachelysanders/7-delicious-cocktails-to-serve-anyone-who-loves-batman?bffbfood&utm_term=4ldqphi#.aveLdLPPg</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/pgvvU9o</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[veniadmeamfra]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Gyroscopes in space</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/VN6sQUT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AURHwmk.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>@europeanspaceagency</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/VN6sQUT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ithinkimbetterthanyousometimes]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Got away with it</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Wq2c6dR</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bJCYUpK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Wq2c6dR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[tanac1esbonny119]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Zelensky through the years</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/yxHoDOB</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1rMmr7k.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I love him  The first real superhero in my lifetime.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/yxHoDOB</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mfrybeasley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Hello there</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NcnYKYm</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/u4NSz1g.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NcnYKYm</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[CamelEnamel]]></dc:creator></item><item>